description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Case Manager x 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Registered Nurse Mental Health or Registered Learning Disability Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MH, LD, A &amp; CAMHS Commissioning Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per week: 37.5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Type: Full Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fixed term or secondment (Secondment considered with employers permission)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a motivated and enthusiastic Registered Nurse Mental Health / Registered Nurse Learning Disability working as a member of the NHS Lincolnshire CCG Operational Commissioning Team. Using a range of tools such as the Continuing Health Care Framework you will assess and review patients with complex needs and associated health problems. You will commission health packages of care for patients. This will also include patients that may be detained under a Mental Health Act Section who are placed out of area and require monitoring and repatriation. You will have substantial experience in either primary, secondary/tertiary Mental Health or Learning Disability care. You will have IT skills, good communication skills; you will need to communicate with all stakeholders including GPs and all Multidisciplinary team members. You will be reliable, flexible and a team worker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is offered as a fixed term or secondment, 37.5 hours a week, over 5 days Monday to Friday.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please contact Julie Betts for more information on 07920 710 508 or email julie.betts@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date – 13/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date- 17/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
